 0076:     majorAxis : List-like
 0077:         List-like normalized coordinate direction of major axis; [x,y]
 0078:     minorAxis : List-like

 0081:         Length of major axis.
 0082:     minorRadii : float

 0089:     info : bool, optional, default: True

static char __pyx_doc_8aligater_8AGCython_2gateThreshold[] = "\n    Threshold gating function. Can be called with one or two markers which affects plotting.\n\n    Call with two markers to get a two dimensional view or with one col which will instead show a density plot.\n    \n    **Parameters**\n    \n    fcs : AGClasses.AGSample object\n        Flow data loaded in an sample object.\n    xCol : str\n        Marker label.\n    yCol : str, optional, default: None\n        Marker label. If specified, opts for a two dimensional view when plotting. Otherwise, a density plot.\n    thresh : float\n        Threshold for cutoff, see orientation and population parameters for how this is applied.\n    orientation, str, optional, default: 'vertical'\n        If two markers are passed this parameter decies if the cut is made on the x- or y-axis.\n\n        'vertical' corresponds to drawing a vertical line in the plot, i.e. cut-off is applied to the x-axis.\n        'horisontal' corresponds to drawing a horisontal line in the plot, i.e. cut-off is applied to the y-axis.\n    population, str, optional, default: 'upper'\n        This parameter determines which population should be returned.\n\n        'upper' means any events with a value above the treshold are returned.\n\n        'lower' means any events with a value below the treshold will be returned.\n\n        The default value means the population that's considered 'positive' in flow cytometry terms is returned.\n    parentGate : AGgate object, optional\n        Parent population to apply the gating to. \n        If no AGgate object is passed gating is applied to the ungated data frame.\n    scale : str, optional, default: 'linear'\n        If plotting enabled, which scale to be used on both axis.\n    T : int, optional, default: 1000\n        If plotting enabled and scale is logish, the threshold for linear-loglike transition\n    filePlot : str, optional, default: None\n        Option to plot the gate to file to specified path. \n\n        Warning: might overwrite stuff.    \n    Q""C : bool, optional, default: False\n        If True, adds a downsampled image of the gating view to the gate object. These can be collected by an AGExperiment object if it's QC flag is also True.\n        \n    **Returns**\n\n    AGClasses.AGgate object\n         Returns an AGgate object for the gated population.\n\n    **Examples**\n\n    None currently.\n    ";

 0172:     """
 0173:     Threshold gating function. Can be called with one or two markers which affects plotting.\n
 0174:     Call with two markers to get a two dimensional view or with one col which will instead show a density plot.
 0175:     
 0176:     **Parameters**
 0177:     
 0178:     fcs : AGClasses.AGSample object
 0179:         Flow data loaded in an sample object.
 0180:     xCol : str
 0181:         Marker label.
 0182:     yCol : str, optional, default: None
 0183:         Marker label. If specified, opts for a two dimensional view when plotting. Otherwise, a density plot.
 0184:     thresh : float
 0185:         Threshold for cutoff, see orientation and population parameters for how this is applied.
 0186:     orientation, str, optional, default: 'vertical'
 0187:         If two markers are passed this parameter decies if the cut is made on the x- or y-axis.\n
 0188:         'vertical' corresponds to drawing a vertical line in the plot, i.e. cut-off is applied to the x-axis.
 0189:         'horisontal' corresponds to drawing a horisontal line in the plot, i.e. cut-off is applied to the y-axis.
 0190:     population, str, optional, default: 'upper'
 0191:         This parameter determines which population should be returned.\n
 0192:         'upper' means any events with a value above the treshold are returned.\n
 0193:         'lower' means any events with a value below the treshold will be returned.\n
 0194:         The default value means the population that's considered 'positive' in flow cytometry terms is returned.
 0195:     parentGate : AGgate object, optional
 0196:         Parent population to apply the gating to. 
 0197:         If no AGgate object is passed gating is applied to the ungated data frame.
 0198:     scale : str, optional, default: 'linear'
 0199:         If plotting enabled, which scale to be used on both axis.
 0200:     T : int, optional, default: 1000
 0201:         If plotting enabled and scale is logish, the threshold for linear-loglike transition
 0202:     filePlot : str, optional, default: None
 0203:         Option to plot the gate to file to specified path. \n
 0204:         Warning: might overwrite stuff.    
 0205:     QC : bool, optional, default: False
 0206:         If True, adds a downsampled image of the gating view to the gate object. These can be collected by an AGExperiment object if it's QC flag is also True.
 0207:         
 0208:     **Returns**
 0209: 
 0210:     AGClasses.AGgate object
 0211:          Returns an AGgate object for the gated population.
 0212: 
 0213:     **Examples**
 0214: 
 0215:     None currently.
 0216:     """
